message.content:
cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.SY, cs.IT, cs.SE 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on the impact of signal jamming attacks on wireless communication in CBTC systems. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is also likely as the paper discusses countermeasures to limit the impact of the attacks. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as CBTC supports train operation automation and moving-block signaling, which are control systems. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is relevant as the paper discusses the use of frequency hopping spread spectrum as a countermeasure. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is less likely but still possible as the paper develops a FHSS repeater prototype using software-defined radios.
